deck: A 10-issues series that tells the story of a young white teenager in China.
description: At 14 year oldl, He Pao attends the massacre of her adoptive parents by Yu Kong, a son of bourgeois who suddenly descended into madness. Hidden under men's clothing and decided to find and punish the murderer, she begins to walk alone the roads of medieval China the twelfth century. Some time hosted by nuns, she finally found Yu Kong became a disciple of the Mad Monk. He Pao, fascinated by the monk decides to uncover its secrets. The girl grows and with it the desire to penetrate the mystery of his childhood. Vink told and brilliantly illustrates the history of the original and independent complex character who refuses to integrate the various companies met during his adventures.
name: Le Moine Fou

deck: The Adventures of He Pao (Le Moine Fou) continues in this volume.
description: He Pao returns in a new series that absorbs and extends that of Le Moine Fou. Her wanderings led her to a village where girls mysteriously disappear. He Pao could not avoid this threat if she was'nt the holder of the martial art of the mad monk, giving her (among other) superhuman physical strength. But even that does not preserve the horror of it located at the end of the road.
name: Les Voyages de He Pao
